<TITLE> Bashundhara City says fire loss over Tk 200 crore </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Mar 15 (bdnews24.com) - Bashundhara City's management said Sunday damage due to Friday's fire could top Tk 200 crore. General manager (administration) of the country's biggest shopping complex, Kamrul Mehedi, told reporters it would reopen to public on Monday. "Structural damage was huge on the top floors that caught fire," he said. "But the shopping mall on the lower floors was safe as it was at a safe distance," he added. Earlier in the afternoon, the probe committee formed to investigate the devastating blaze visited the site. bdnew
